description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locum Consultant Psychiatrist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Adult Intensive Case Management in Psychosis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Erith Centre, Park Crescent, Erith, Kent, DA8 3EE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£82,096 - £110,683 plus £2,162 LW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;24 hours / 6 PAs per week. Fixed Term 12 months in the first instance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Potential for more hours as per discussion with the Clinical Director&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxleas NHS Foundation Trust, formed in April 1995, is a provider of mental health services for children, adults and older adults in Bromley, Bexley and Greenwich, and a specialist provider of Forensic and Challenging Behaviour services for Bexley, Greenwich, Lewisham, North Southwark, Bromley, and Learning Disability Services for Greenwich, Bexley and Bromley. The Trust also provides Community health services in Bexley and Greenwich and a wide range of health (physical and mental health) in prisons across Kent and London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following an internal re-organisation, we are seeking to recruit a Locum Consultant in General Adult Psychiatry for the Bexley Community Mental Health Team to provide support and leadership to the ICMP service. The post holder will be part of an establishment of three full time Consultants within the Bexley Local Care Network (LCN) Teams managing a range of patient clinic types.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is potential for this post to become part of the permanent establishment in due course.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to developing the careers of our medical staff and the successful applicant will be encouraged to participate fully in the continuing medical education programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interested applicants should contact Dr Derek Tracy, Clinical Director to discuss their specific requirements. Email derek.tracy@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
